suggestions.description:
App.jsx line 798 declares handleTabKeyDown as a plain arrow function inside the App component body. It closes over `tab` and `setTab` but is re-created on every render — every single state change in App (polling updates every 30s, timer ticks every 60s, isSyncing, confetti, etc.) produces a new function reference. Both tab buttons receive it via onKeyDown, meaning those buttons see prop changes on every App render even if nothing else about them changed.

Fix:
  const handleTabKeyDown = useCallback((e) => {
    const currentIdx = TABS.indexOf(tab)
    if (e.key === 'ArrowRight' || e.key === 'ArrowDown') {
      e.preventDefault()
      const next = TABS[(currentIdx + 1) % TABS.length]
      setTab(next)
      history.replaceState(null, '', '#' + next)
    } else if (e.key === 'ArrowLeft' || e.key === 'ArrowUp') {
      e.preventDefault()
      const prev = TABS[(currentIdx - 1 + TABS.length) % TABS.length]
      setTab(prev)
      history.replaceState(null, '', '#' + prev)
    }
  }, [tab])

Visible in the #81 mobile screenshot: Bloberto's speech bubble ('Knew all along...') renders over the tab selector row, making the Dashboard tab button partially obscured. The speech bubble uses CSS positioning relative to the character inside the office floor, but the office floor sits below the tab bar — speech bubbles that pop upward can overlap the tab bar when they grow tall enough.

Fix: Add a max-height or overflow:hidden on the speech bubble, or clamp the top position so it can't escape the .office-floor bounds. Alternatively, give the tab bar a z-index higher than the office floor's speech bubbles:
  .tab-toggle { position: relative; z-index: 10; }
  .speech-bubble { max-bottom: calc(100% of office-floor); }
